# The Dwarves had two [[glottal consonant]]s: {{IPA|/h/}} and {{IPA|/ʔ/}}, the latter being the [[glottal stop|glottal]] beginning of a word with an initial vowel. Thus, in need of a reversible cirth to represent these sounds, they switched [[Image:Certh 54.svg|16px]] and [[Image:Certh 34.svg|16px]], giving the first the value {{IPA|/s/}} and using the second for {{IPA|/h/}} and its reversed counterpart [[Image:Certh 35.svg|16px]] for {{IPA|/ʔ/}}.
# These cirth where a halved form of [[Image:Certh 46.svg|16px]], used for vowels like those in the word "b''u''tt''e''r". [[Image:Certh 55.svg|16px]] represented a schwa sound {{IPA|/ə/}} in unstressed syllables, while [[Image:Certh 56.svg|16px]] represented {{IPA|/ʌ/}}, a sound similar to the schwa, only in stressed syllables. When weak they were reduced to a stroke without a stem ([[Image:Certh 55a.svg|16px]], [[Image:Certh 56a.svg|16px]]).
# This sign is to denote [[Aspirated consonant|aspiration]] in voiceless stops, occurring frequently in Khuzdul.

* For unknown reasons, the Dwarves also dropped the cirth [[Image:Certh 14.svg|16px]] {{IPA|/dʒ/}}, [[Image:Certh 16.svg|16px]] {{IPA|/ʒ/}} and for those sounds they substituted [[Image:Certh 29.svg|16px]] and [[Image:Certh 30.svg|16px]] which the Elves used for {{IPA|/r/}} and {{IPA|/r̥/}}.
* Subsequently, the Dwarves used [[Image:Certh 12.svg|16px]] for {{IPA|/ʀ/, /ʁ/}} which had the value of {{IPA|/n/}} by the Elves; then for the sound of {{IPA|/n/}}, they chose the certh [[Image:Certh 22.svg|16px]] which the Elves used for the sound {{IPA|/ŋ/}}, useless in Khuzdul.
* They also invented the new certh [[Image:Certh 53.svg|16px]], used as an alternative, simplified (and, maybe, weaker) form of [[Image:Certh 22.svg|16px]]. Inspired by the visual relation of those two letters, they gave [[Image:Certh 17.svg|16px]] the value of {{IPA|/z/}} to relate better with [[Image:Certh 54.svg|16px]] that had, by then, the value {{IPA|/s/}}.<ref>[http://tolkiengateway.net/wiki/Angerthas_Moria "Angerthas Moria"] on Tolkien Gateway wiki.</ref>

==Angerthas Erebor==
According to [[Tolkien's legendarium]], after the [[Second Age]], the Cirth were obsoleted by the [[Tengwar]] among the western races and remained in use only by Dwarves and Men. The Dwarves developed even pen-written cursive forms, since they used them exclusively in any form of writing communication, even in paper. At the beginning of the [[Third Age]], the Dwarves were driven out of Moria. Some migrated to the [[Ered Mithrin|Grey Mountains]], some to the [[Iron Hills]] and [[Thráin I]] came to [[Lonely Mountain|Erebor]]. There he founded his Dwarf-kingdom. There the ''Angerthas Moria'' was modified further and some new cirth were added, but some reverted to their Elvish usage, thus creating the '''''Angerthas Erebor''''' variation. This mode was used in [[Westron]] by Dwarves.<ref name="Angerthas Erebor">[http://tolkiengateway.net/wiki/Angerthas_Erebor "Angerthas Erebor"] on Tolkien Gateway wiki.</ref>

Many cirth here stand for sounds not occurring in Khuzdul (at least in published words of Khuzdul: of course, our corpus is very limited to judge the necessity or not, of these sounds). Here they are marked with a black star (<sup>★</sup>).

